See?

518
01:04:08,386 --> 01:04:09,803
[Bells tolling]

519
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:25,569
Good evening.

520
01:04:28,948 --> 01:04:31,116
You're with the Illuminati.

521
01:04:34,078 --> 01:04:35,453
Beg your pardon?

522
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:39,124
There's no such thing.
It's just a bedtime story.

523
01:04:46,549 --> 01:04:47,966
Illuminati.

524
01:04:49,468 --> 01:04:51,386
The people of the light.

525
01:04:53,764 --> 01:04:55,765
Have you brought my triangle?

526
01:04:56,183 --> 01:05:00,103
No, of course you haven't.
You've hidden it somewhere.

527
01:05:01,606 --> 01:05:03,899
Well, you can keep the triangle
you have...

528
01:05:04,442 --> 01:05:08,069
and I will keep your father's clock,
and we can be partners.

529
01:05:08,321 --> 01:05:10,030
Who sits here?

530
01:05:12,074 --> 01:05:14,409
We can be partners
and go for the big prize...

531
01:05:15,369 --> 01:05:16,953
the Triangle of Light.

532
01:05:16,996 --> 01:05:19,915
Yes, but who sits here?

533
01:05:21,042 --> 01:05:24,502
It's an incredible dream,
an awesome power.

534
01:05:25,212 --> 01:05:27,172
It could set right so many wrongs.

535
01:05:29,050 --> 01:05:31,217
I don't think you sit here, do you?

536
01:05:42,438 --> 01:05:44,272
I sit here...

537
01:05:45,232 --> 01:05:47,692
on God's right hand, as it were.

538
01:05:49,904 --> 01:05:51,029
In fact...

539
01:05:51,113 --> 01:05:55,116
I now sit exactly where your father sat.

540
01:05:59,455 --> 01:06:00,622
You're lying.

541
01:06:01,165 --> 01:06:05,710
No. No, he mentored me in the order.

542
01:06:07,797 --> 01:06:09,381
It was truly an honor.

543
01:06:10,758 --> 01:06:12,300
I don't believe you.

544
01:06:14,428 --> 01:06:15,971
My father was not with the Illuminati.

545
01:06:16,055 --> 01:06:18,723
-He would have told me.
-He had a great many secrets.

546
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:23,895
Not from me.

547
01:06:24,563 --> 01:06:26,189
Especially from you.

548
01:06:31,195 --> 01:06:32,821
I know what you want, Lara.

549
01:06:34,073 --> 01:06:35,615
Oh, I doubt it.

550
01:06:45,126 --> 01:06:47,335
Another life with your father...

551
01:06:48,379 --> 01:06:50,130
a second chance.

552
01:06:50,923 --> 01:06:53,425
It'll be within my power to give.

553
01:06:54,802 --> 01:06:57,012
The triangle gives its possessor...

554
01:06:58,431 --> 01:07:00,265
the power of God...

555
01:07:00,641 --> 01:07:05,520
to move back and forth through time,
undo the past.

556
01:07:06,647 --> 01:07:10,650
Help me, and you will get
what I know you want...

557
01:07:11,027 --> 01:07:13,236
to have your father returned to you.

558
01:07:17,825 --> 01:07:20,869
And how do I know
once I gave you that piece...

559
01:07:21,120 --> 01:07:23,413
that you wouldn't then just try to kill me?

560
01:07:26,625 --> 01:07:29,127
Would it make it easier for you...

561
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:33,548
on more familiar ground,
if I killed you now?

562
01:07:35,718 --> 01:07:37,343
Will you reconsider?

563
01:07:59,825 --> 01:08:00,825
[Door banging]

564
01:08:24,016 --> 01:08:25,433
[Speaking in Italian]

565
01:08:38,531 --> 01:08:41,407
-Hello, Alex.
-I suppose you think...

566
01:08:41,492 --> 01:08:43,326
I'm a greedy, unscrupulous sellout...

567
01:08:43,369 --> 01:08:46,329
-and do about anything for money.
-Yes, that's right.

568
01:08:48,249 --> 01:08:50,166
Well, the money bit's true, I guess.

569
01:08:54,713 --> 01:08:56,506
Is it, Alex?

570
01:08:56,841 --> 01:09:00,802
If you cross me,
we may not be able to remain friends.

571
01:09:02,555 --> 01:09:03,555
[Sighing]

572
01:09:05,516 --> 01:09:07,058
Always a pleasure.

573
01:09:08,769 --> 01:09:09,769
[Groaning]

574
01:09:10,980 --> 01:09:12,605
Now for a cold shower.

575
01:09:14,066 --> 01:09:15,483
PIMMS: I think we're in big trouble.

576
01:09:15,568 --> 01:09:16,901
-Hold this, will you?
-Thank you.

577
01:09:17,153 --> 01:09:20,572
They.... They already think that we have
Lady Croft's piece of the triangle.

578
01:09:20,614 --> 01:09:23,575
Yes. They think it's in that box
you're carrying right now.

579
01:09:25,452 --> 01:09:26,661
Is it?

580
01:09:26,829 --> 01:09:28,580
Why don't you worry
about something else?

581
01:09:28,664 --> 01:09:30,165
Of course it's not.

582
01:09:30,958 --> 01:09:34,752
I don't understand. What chance of
success do we have without the piece?

583
01:09:35,087 --> 01:09:37,297
Zero. Don't dwell on it.

584
01:09:37,381 --> 01:09:38,464
But....

585
01:09:42,595 --> 01:09:43,761
Lady Croft.

586
01:09:46,265 --> 01:09:47,974
What a nice surprise.

587
01:09:50,603 --> 01:09:52,020
Thank you.

588
01:09:54,815 --> 01:09:57,734
Now, time to save
the universe again then, is it?

589
01:09:57,943 --> 01:09:59,402
Absolutely.

590
01:10:33,896 --> 01:10:36,606
Are we sure she's really necessary?

591
01:10:37,483 --> 01:10:40,693
Well, one tomb raider is good.
Two, better.

592
01:10:49,286 --> 01:10:52,789
Me bum's gone to sleep again,
all down the left cheek.

593
01:10:52,915 --> 01:10:55,333
Really? That's fascinating.

594
01:11:01,674 --> 01:11:03,758
-How much longer?
-A few hours.

595
01:11:04,260 --> 01:11:06,469
We have to take the last hour over land.

596
01:11:06,512 --> 01:11:09,013
Helicopters won't fly
near the ruined city.

597
01:11:10,849 --> 01:11:12,183
It's a dead zone.

598
01:11:54,268 --> 01:11:56,561
We take all doggies.

599
01:11:57,730 --> 01:12:00,148
Much-o U.S. greenback.

600
01:12:01,233 --> 01:12:02,734
All doggies.

601
01:12:06,405 --> 01:12:07,739
[Dogs whimpering]

602
01:12:25,883 --> 01:12:30,887
[Speaking in Russian]

603
01:12:48,864 --> 01:12:50,031
[Dog barking]

604
01:13:35,119 --> 01:13:36,911
[Chattering in Russian over radio]

605
01:13:56,432 --> 01:13:58,057
Welcome to the dead zone.

606
01:14:13,574 --> 01:14:15,700
It's not a country. It's an ice cube!

607
01:14:19,371 --> 01:14:20,955
MAN: Come on!

608
01:15:19,556 --> 01:15:20,765
[Tone resonating]

609
01:15:49,670 --> 01:15:51,796
All right. Let's go.

610
01:16:44,975 --> 01:16:46,350
MAN: Go on, get it!

611
01:16:54,151 --> 01:16:55,651
Holy shit.

612
01:16:57,571 --> 01:17:01,782
It's a time storm. Time is broken here.

613
01:17:02,034 --> 01:17:05,703
We must find the eye! All of you! Hurry!

614
01:17:06,038 --> 01:17:08,956
We're running out of time! Hurry! Hurry!

615
01:17:17,883 --> 01:17:19,425
[Dogs whimpering]

616
01:17:28,393 --> 01:17:29,602
It's begun.

617
01:17:32,856 --> 01:17:35,191
$50 says the piece is inside the sun.

618
01:17:54,461 --> 01:17:55,461
[Screaming]

619
01:18:18,944 --> 01:18:22,988
MAN: For God's sake, hurry! The eclipse
will be over in a few minutes!

620
01:18:30,288 --> 01:18:33,290
Alex, give me the clock.
I know what to do.

621
01:19:16,668 --> 01:19:17,668
Lara!

622
01:19:28,180 --> 01:19:29,680
Has she got the piece?

623
01:19:33,143 --> 01:19:34,769
[Dogs whimpering and howling]

624
01:19:40,150 --> 01:19:41,525
We will now...

625
01:19:41,610 --> 01:19:44,153
unite these two parts...

626
01:19:44,696 --> 01:19:47,364
the past and the present.

627
01:19:48,533 --> 01:19:51,660
At last, we of the Illuminati...

628
01:19:51,745 --> 01:19:55,247
will control time
and fulfill the sacred promise...

629
01:19:55,415 --> 01:19:56,957
to our ancestors.

630
01:19:57,542 --> 01:20:01,670
-Soon, the entire world will bow--
-Enough of this twaddle.

631
01:20:07,719 --> 01:20:08,928
Go on! Go on!

632
01:20:36,039 --> 01:20:38,374
ALEX: Not quite what you hoped for,
Mr. Powell?

633
01:20:43,046 --> 01:20:44,171
Lara...

634
01:20:46,091 --> 01:20:48,342
I have a gut instinct about this.

635
01:20:50,095 --> 01:20:52,763
After all, you are the daughter
of a genius.

636
01:20:52,931 --> 01:20:54,557
Let me test my theory.

637
01:21:14,578 --> 01:21:15,578
[Groaning]

638
01:21:45,984 --> 01:21:49,653
You had to let him go.
No more bubbles.

639
01:21:50,572 --> 01:21:52,865
You show me
how to complete the triangle...

640
01:21:53,617 --> 01:21:55,492
we can change his fate.

641
01:21:56,661 --> 01:22:00,331
If you deliver me the power of God,
I will spare him.

642
01:22:00,999 --> 01:22:02,917
It's only a little trip back in time.

643
01:22:03,710 --> 01:22:08,380
But I'm pretty sure you've figured out
the answer to the problem.

644
01:22:10,091 --> 01:22:13,510
And then, of course,
there's the loss of your father.

645
01:22:13,845 --> 01:22:15,220
I can change that.

646
01:22:29,861 --> 01:22:31,695
You'd better be ready for this.

647
01:22:36,868 --> 01:22:40,704
-Unhook your laser sight.
-Do it.

648
01:23:17,701 --> 01:23:20,160
"To see a world in a grain of sand."

649
01:23:47,939 --> 01:23:49,189
[Groaning]

650
01:23:53,278 --> 01:23:54,445
Daddy?

651
01:23:59,451 --> 01:24:00,451
Lara.

652
01:24:03,788 --> 01:24:05,039
Is this real?

653
01:24:07,167 --> 01:24:08,625
It is a crossing...

654
01:24:09,794 --> 01:24:11,920
of my past and your present.

655
01:24:12,672 --> 01:24:14,882
Why did you not tell me
about the Illuminati?

656
01:24:15,508 --> 01:24:17,217
You were only a child.

657
01:24:17,302 --> 01:24:19,136
You could have written in yourjournals.

658
01:24:19,220 --> 01:24:23,182
-You never mentioned it, not once.
-Lara, I burst to tell you everything.

659
01:24:23,641 --> 01:24:26,018
But in the fierceness
of my own battles...

660
01:24:26,102 --> 01:24:28,896
I strove to tell you
only that which would inspire you...

661
01:24:28,980 --> 01:24:30,564
and keep you safe.

662
01:24:31,858 --> 01:24:33,817
I love you so much.

663
01:24:35,153 --> 01:24:36,653
But I've missed you.

664
01:24:38,073 --> 01:24:39,823
And I have missed you.

665
01:24:43,078 --> 01:24:44,995
I know why you came here...

666
01:24:45,038 --> 01:24:48,332
why you took the power of the light,
but this must not happen.

667
01:24:48,666 --> 01:24:52,211
Why? Why can't we use the power
just this once?

668
01:24:54,172 --> 01:24:55,672
Why can't you stay?

669
01:24:56,299 --> 01:24:58,926
We can't change time.

670
01:25:00,220 --> 01:25:02,137
But time was stolen from us...

671
01:25:04,516 --> 01:25:06,016
and it's not fair.

672
01:25:06,518 --> 01:25:08,685
No, it's not fair.

673
01:25:09,687 --> 01:25:11,772
But you have stolen time itself...

674
01:25:12,482 --> 01:25:14,775
and you must give it back.

675
01:25:16,528 --> 01:25:18,862
You must destroy the triangle.

676
01:25:21,032 --> 01:25:22,783
Suddenly I feel so alone.

677
01:25:24,160 --> 01:25:28,997
You're never alone. I am with you
always, just as I've always been.

678
01:26:56,377 --> 01:26:57,377
No.

679
01:27:11,643 --> 01:27:12,976
Move out!

680
01:27:17,649 --> 01:27:19,149
[Groaning]

681
01:27:22,445 --> 01:27:23,528
Lara.

682
01:27:25,406 --> 01:27:26,490
Wait!

683
01:27:27,992 --> 01:27:29,701
Your father begged for his life...

684
01:27:29,786 --> 01:27:31,745
when we caught him betraying us.

685
01:27:31,829 --> 01:27:34,539
He pleaded like a baby.

686
01:27:34,624 --> 01:27:35,874
Surrender.

687
01:27:38,002 --> 01:27:39,253
Never.

688
01:27:42,799 --> 01:27:47,386
He seemed particularly concerned
that I shouldn't take this.

689
01:27:53,101 --> 01:27:56,353
ALEX: Lara, no!
The place is coming down!

690
01:27:56,396 --> 01:27:59,398
-This is insane!
-Get them out of here.

691
01:28:04,362 --> 01:28:05,696
You just hurry.

692
01:28:12,161 --> 01:28:13,161
[Chuckling]

693
01:28:17,875 --> 01:28:19,459
There you go...

694
01:28:19,877 --> 01:28:21,295
safe and sound.

695
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:33,890
No guns.

696
01:31:25,480 --> 01:31:27,230
[Humming]

697
01:31:29,609 --> 01:31:30,609
[Clattering]

698
01:31:31,611 --> 01:31:32,861
Oh, my God!

699
01:31:35,907 --> 01:31:37,324
Quiet.

700
01:31:41,704 --> 01:31:43,413
[Bird chirping]

701
01:32:10,691 --> 01:32:11,775
What?

702
01:32:15,613 --> 01:32:16,947
[Mechanical whirring]
